<HEADLINE> Standing Committee Member Visits Chinese Law Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) - Wei Jianxing, a member of the
Standing Committee of the Communist Party of China Central
Committee's Political Bureau, said today that Chinese lawyers
should get a better education in professional ethics and
regulations to improve their overall quality.
</P>
<P>
Wei made the remarks while visiting an exhibition on the
achievements of Chinese lawyers, in Beijing's Museum of the
Chinese History, which is sponsored by the Ministry of Justice.
</P>
<P>
He said that the exhibition is significant in displaying the
development of the law and its achievements since the beginning of
country's reform and opening up drive, and that lawyers should
contribute to the country's reforms and development efforts.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition shows the important role that lawyers are
playing in China's political, economic, and social life, using
photos, statistics, and individual cases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
