<HEADLINE> Croatians Superstitious Confronting Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANTES, France, June 17 (Xinhua) -- A 3-1 victory against Jamaica
has made Croatians superstitious before meeting Japan on June here on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The day before their Group H opener in Lens last Sunday, the
Croatians trained immediately after their arrival.
</P>
<P>
"That seemed to work for us, given that we won the match," said a
spokesperson for the team on Wednesday. "We'll repeat this method
against Japan in Nantes in the hope of obtaining another victory."
</P>
<P>
The Croatians will assemble at La Beaujoire stadium here on Friday
afternoon, only an hour and twenty minutes after their expected
landing at the Nantes-Atlantique airport. 
</P>
</TEXT>
