<HEADLINE> Japan Donates Training Equipment to Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's Posts and
Telecommunications Corporation (PTC) Wednesday received training
equipment worth 1.5 million U.S. Dollars from the Japanese
government.
</P>
<P>
Takawo Shibata, Minister-Counselor of the Embassy of Japan to
Zimbabwe, officially handed over the equipment to Zimbabwean
Telecommunications and Information Minister Chen Chimutengwende
at the PTC Training Center here, the Zimbabwe News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Shibata said that "the equipment was donated with a view to
assisting the PTC's ongoing digitalization and expansion program
which Japan has been actively supporting."
</P>
<P>
He said many PTC technicians underwent training courses in
Japan on the latest innovations in the telecommunications
industry.
</P>
<P>
Chimutengwende said: "It has always been our wish that this
training unit have all the equipment that it needs so as to train
first-class people to improve the efficiency, maintenance and
installation at the PTC." 
</P>
