<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Scot Calderwood to Probably Miss Rest of Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MARSEILLE, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Scotland defender Colin Calderwood,
who broke bones in his hand in Tuesday's 1-1 draw with Norway, would
probably miss the rest of the World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
The 33-year-old center-back, who plays for English club Tottenham,
had returned to London for an operation on his hand.
</P>
<P>
Scotland team doctor Stewart Hillis said on Wednesday in Scotland's
training camp in Avignon that Calderwood has sustained two broken
bones in his right hand, with one of them misplaced.
</P>
<P>
"He is unlikely to play in the rest of the tournament," said
Hillis.
</P>
<P>
Scotland head coach Craig Brown said Calderwood's missing would be
a setback for the team.
</P>
<P>
Captain Colin Hendry also sustained a groin strain but is expected
to recover in time for next Tuesday's crunch game against Morocco.
</P>
</TEXT>
