<HEADLINE> Chubais Appointed Presidential Envoy for Finance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Anatoly Chubais has been appointed
by a decree of Russian President Boris Yeltsin the president's
special envoy for liaison with the international financial
agencies in the rank of Vice-Prime Minister, the Interfax news
agency reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Chubais, the former first vice-prime minister, is Chairman of
United Energy Systems of Russia.
</P>
<P>
Presidential spokesman Sergei Yastrzhembsky quoted the decree
as saying that in exercising the functions entrusted to him and in
interacting with federal executive authorities, the Central Bank
and international financial organizations, "the special envoy will
have the rights of a deputy prime minister."
</P>
<P>
According to the decree, he said, the envoy "will coordinate
activity of the executive branch, the Central Bank of Russia, and
Russia's representatives in international organizations, working
out and implementing state policy toward international financial
bodies on foreign borrowing and other issues."
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Sergei Kiriyenko who is attending the second
economic forum in St. Petersburg said that Chubais is a good
choice for the president's envoy to Russia's talks with
international finance institutions.
</P>
<P>
He noted there is a need for "coordination among all branches
of government in dealing with international financial
organizations."
</P>
<P>
Kiriyenko said,"Chubais has rich experience of contacts with
international financial institutions and can be very useful in our
work with these organizations."  
</P>
