<HEADLINE> Dramtic Equaliser Saves Austria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SAINT-ETIENNE, June 17 (Xinhua) -- A dramatic equaliser at the
injury time again saved Austria in the match against Chile.
</P>
<P>
Salas punched in a rebound after Zamorano's header was blocked
by Austrian goal-keeper Michael Konsel at the 53rd minute.
</P>
<P>
The Austrian team, which forced Cameroon to a 1-1 draw thanks to
a last-minute equaliser in their first group match, didn't give up
and this time it was Ivica Vastic who came to the team's rescue.
</P>
<P>
Vastic chipped home the ball to savage the draw for Austria at the
injury time and that left the two teams with two points each from as
many games.
</P>
<P>
The first half of the match was boring with both teams nervous
on the pitch.
</P>
<P>
But the Chilean team took an upper hand in the second half when
Salas and Zamorano combination posed greater threat towards the
Austrian goal.
</P>
<P>
At the 53rd minute, Austrian goal-keeper Konsel blocked a
Zamorano header but Salas punched in the rebound with his leg to
give Chile the 1-0 lead.
</P>
<P>
Zamorano had the golden chance to secure the victory for Chile
but his shot was tipped off by Konsel at the 88th minute.
</P>
<P>
The Austrian team, knowing the remaining time was limited, still
kept their pace and built up their attacks patiently. Their efforts
finally paid off when second-half substitute Vastic got the
equaliser.
</P>
<P>
Later on Wednesday, Italy will play Cameroon at Montpellier in
the other Group B match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
