<HEADLINE> Luxembourg PM Meets Chinese NPC Vice-Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUXEMBOURG, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Luxembourg Prime Minister
Jean-Claude Juncker met on Wednesday Jiang Chunyun, vice-chairman
of the Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's
Congress (NPC), the country's legislature.
</P>
<P>
The Luxembourg prime minister recalled his pleasant stay not
long ago in Beijing on his way to a visit in Mongolia and his
fruitful talks in Beijing with Chinese NPC Chairman Li Peng and
Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji.
</P>
<P>
Juncker said: "The visit by Chinese legislators will positively
boost the development of bilateral relations between Luxembourg
and China."
</P>
