of the Chinese and Luxembourg peoples and governments to build up
bilateral ties on the existing sound foundation.
</P>
<P>
China and Luxembourg, Jiang said, should complement each other
with their respective strengths, broaden cooperation in economy
and trade, enhance exchange and cooperation in finance and create
better conditions for the cooperation among small and medium-sized
enterprises of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The NPC vice-chairman added that the visit by senior Chinese
lawmakers was an important component of the effort to enhance
bilateral ties and the four-day visit to Luxembourg helped to
deepen mutual understanding and cement friendship.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese lawmakers delegation left here late on Wednesday
for Strasbourg for an official visit to the European Parliament
that is seated in the French city.  
