<DOCNO> XIE19980618.0035 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania Tries to Restore the Capital Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 17 (Xinhua) -- From today on, securities
companies with a nominal capital below 35,000 U.S. dollars are not
authorized to operate as intermediaries on the Romanian capital
market.
</P>
<P>
The new regulations, which come into effect on Wednesday, are
meant to strengthen the financial power of the operators and to
increase the confidence in Romanian capital market, stated Stefan
Boboc, President of the National Securities Commission(NSC).
</P>
<P>
Stefan Boboc appealed for more measures to be taken to restore
the local capital market. "The constitution of a national fund for
guaranteeing investments in securities made by individuals, like
the one constituted for guaranteeing the bank deposits, would lead
to the development of investment funds and would stimulate
individuals to invest in shares", he said.
</P>
<P>
This way, in case of bankruptcy of a securities company, the
individuals who had invested through the respective company would
be able to recuperate the money they invested, or least a
percentage of the money, the President of NSC added.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the present downfall of the Romanian capital
market, Stefan Boboc said that this situation has foreign causes,
mostly the distrust of foreign investors in emerging markets.
</P>
<P>
Strengthening the financial power of the National Agency for
Compensating, Discounting and Depositing is compelling, perhaps
even through a merger of this agency with the independent
shareholders registers, Stefan Boboc stated. In his opinion, this
merger would lead to the constitution of a genuine securities bank
which would offer the shareholders and issuers much more financial
services.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
