<HEADLINE> S. Leonean Rebels Attack Village, Killing 8 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Eight civilians were killed and 18
others wounded in northern Sierra Leone Tuesday when rebels loyal
to the ousted military junta attacked a village near the northern
provincial capital Makeni.
</P>
<P>
The attacked village Kasanba is about 24 miles from Makeni and
has soldiers of the west African peacekeeping force ECOMOG based
there, British Broadcasting Corporation (BBC) reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A witness was quoted by the report as saying that heavily-armed
rebels attacked the village at 6:00 a.m. and began shooting
indiscriminatingly.
</P>
<P>
When ECOMOG troops tried to engage the rebels, they found that
they were outnumbered and had no alternative but to retreat, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Eight fleeing civilians, including a four-year-old girl, were
hacked to death by the rebels, while 18 others wore severe
gunshot wounds, the report added.
</P>
<P>
When villagers came out of the bush Wednesday, they found that
almost all the houses in the village were set ablaze.
</P>
<P>
Troops loyal to the military junta of Major Paul Johnny
Koromah have been engaged in fierce fighting against ECOMOG in
eastern and northern Sierra Leone since mid-February, when they
were chased out of Freetown.
</P>
<P>
ECOMOG sources said earlier that the rebels are now in a
desperate situation as they have run out of food and other
logistic supplies.
</P>
<P>
The rainy season, however, has prevented ECOMOG from a quick
success in its efforts to mop up all the rebels, the sources
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
