<HEADLINE> LIFFE To List Selected Bond Futures On APT For </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The London International Financial
Futures and Options Exchange (LIFFE) announced Wednesday that it
would list certain bond futures onto its Automated Pit Trading
(APT) system for daytime trading.
</P>
<P>
Previously, these contracts have traded on LIFFE's floor during
the trading day.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, as from August 3, 1998, APT will be the sole trading
platform for the contracts of BTP future, Bund future and Five
Year Gilt future.
</P>
<P>
By moving these bond futures contracts onto APT, LIFFE is
responding to strong Member demand for using screen-based systems
for trading particular bond futures.
</P>
<P>
With the introduction of LIFFE Connect for Financial Futures in
Q2 1999, it was announced LIFFE will migrate the relevant bond
contracts from APT onto this new electronic trading platform.
</P>
<P>
Daniel Hodson, LIFFE's Chief Executive said: "By providing
daytime screen-based trading for the BTP, Bund and Five Year Gilt
futures on APT, LIFFE is responding to growing Member demand for
electronic trading of particular bond futures contracts."
</P>
<P>
"It is part of LIFFE's flexible strategy to list its products
on the preferred and most effective platform," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
