had also been reported in parts of Gombe State in the northeast.
</P>
<P>
According to the source, a company might be invited to
undertake the production of nuclear energy once the occurrences
of the mineral in commercial quantities were established.
</P>
<P>
In its effort to exploit the vast potential of the energy
sector, the Nigerian government has established the Nigerian
Uranium Mining Company in partnership with a French company,
under the supervision of the Nigerian Mining Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The project was stalled because the French partners withdrew
at a stage when they feared that a recorded fall in the price of
uranium in the world market meant bad business, the report said,
but did not say when this took place.
</P>
<P>
However, ministry officials were reportedly optimistic that
the uranium mining venture might be reactivated in view of
current development.  
