Djibouti were designated as the peace facilitators of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) in the dispute between
Ethiopia and Eritrea during the 34th OAU summit meeting ended
June 10 in Ouagadougou, Burkina Faso.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman from the Ethiopian Foreign Ministry said here
Wednesday that Rwandan President Pasteur Bezimungou is expected
to arrive here in the evening while the presidents of Djibouti
and Burkina Faso are expected to be here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
