saying that the four African leaders will consult with senior
Ethiopian government officials including Prime Minister Meles
Zenawi.
</P>
<P>
The four leaders, accompanied by OAU Secretary General Salim
Ahmed Salim, will make a similar trip to Eritrea with a view to
peacefully resolving the crisis between the two Horn of Africa
countries, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Ethiopian Foreign Ministry said here Wednesday
that the Eritrean government is attempting to deceive the
international community by saying that the crisis between
Ethiopia and Eritrea is showing improvement following the
moratorium on air strikes.
</P>
<P>
In a press statement sent through its permanent mission to the
United Nations in New York, the Ethiopian Foreign Ministry said
that the unilateral moratorium on air strikes is not "a positive
and first step toward ending the war" as the Eritrean authorities
would like the international community to believe, adding that
the crisis is "in fact worsening by the day."
</P>
<P>
Both Ethiopia and Eritrea agreed last Sunday to accept the
U.S. government proposal to halt air strikes.  
</P>
