<HEADLINE> Tanzania Investment Center Approves 1,000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzania Investment
Center has approved more than 1,000 investment projects since it
was established in 1990.
</P>
<P>
Nassoro Malocho, the Minister of State for Planning and
Parastatal Sector Reform, told the National Assembly Wednesday
that 523 of the approved projects are on industries and 152 are
on tourism.
</P>
<P>
In addition, 85 are on agriculture and livestock, 68 on
natural resources, 56 on transportation, 43 on construction, 38
on minerals, and 35 on social services, according to a report
reaching here from the city of Dodoma, where the parliament is
based.
</P>
<P>
Most of the investors are from Britain, with a number of 314,
Malocho said.
</P>
<P>
Other investors are from Italy, numbering 36, Germany, 20, the
United States, 16, Canada, 15, Kenya, 12, the Netherlands, 12,
Lebanon, 10, Australia, 7, and South Africa, 6.
</P>
<P>
Some of the projects, however, have yet to take off due to
certain problems. He said the Investment Services Division (ISD)
is visiting and inspecting implementation of the projects from
time to time as well as frequently reviewing the reports
submitted to them by investors so as to facilitate the smooth
implementation of the projects.
</P>
<P>
Other relevant departments are also paying close attention to
the development the projects for the sake of economic
development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
