<HEADLINE> Iranian President Opposes Impeachment of Interior </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad Khatami
opposes the impeachment of his Interior Minister Abdollah Nouri,
government spokesman Ataollah Mohajerani said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Khatami has praised Nouri as among the "capable and outstanding
personalities" and criticized the impeachment timing as improper
after 31 Majlis (parliament) hardline members called last week for
impeaching Nouri, the official news agency IRNA quoted Mohajerani
as saying.
</P>
<P>
The lawmakers accused moderate Nouri of creating tensions in
society, making provocative statements and appointing
inexperienced people to managerial positions in his ministry.
</P>
<P>
The impeachment session is scheduled for Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Mohajerani dismissed the allegations by impeachment promoters
that Khatami would change his mind about Nouri once he heard the
lawmakers' report on his performance, saying that it was
impossible Khatami had been unaware of the performance by his most
important cabinet minister.
</P>
<P>
"Abdollah Nouri is capable of defending his principled stands
as well as matters relating to the interior ministry," said
Mohajerani, who is also the Minister of Culture and Islamic
Guidance.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman further criticized the timing of the impeachment
motion which coincided with the visit of Kuwaiti Interior Minister
Sheikh Mohammad Khaled Al-Hamad Al-Sabah.
</P>
<P>
Relations between the two countries warmed up after Khatami
took power last year.
</P>
<P>
The impeachment came at a time when relations between the
moderate government and hardliners in judiciary and parliament
were tense arising from the arrest and trial of Tehran Mayor
Gholamhussein Karbaschi, who was also a loyalist of the president.
</P>
<P>
Moderate factions have described moves launched by hardliners
as attempts aimed at weakening Khatami's government. 
</P>
