Turkey Muhammad Reza as "persona non grata" after he attended a
radical religious rally and allegedly attacked Turkey's secular
system.
</P>
<P>
In retaliation, Tehran asked Turkey to recall its Ambassador to
Iran, sending their relationship to the freezing point.
</P>
<P>
Boladian, for his part, said Iran would make energetic efforts
to further enhance its cooperation with Turkey in various fields.
</P>
<P>
Boladian and his delegation are visiting Ankara to discuss
security issues with their Turkish counterparts.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has repeatedly accused Iran of supporting its outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party, which has been fighting a separatist war
against the government since 1984. 
</P>
