<HEADLINE> Militant Group Ready to Join PNA: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 17 (Xinhua) -- A leading Palestinian militant
organization that opposes peace with Israel announced Wednesday to
join the Palestinian self-rule government, an offspring of the
peace process.
</P>
<P>
The Islamic Jihad (Holy War), headed by Abu Samra, made the
announcement in Gaza on the second day of the ongoing political
consultations held by Palestinian National Authority (PNA) with
opposition political parties.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was carried by Jerusalem Media and
Communications Center, an East Jerusalem-based Palestinian news
service. The report, giving no details, has not been independently
confirmed.
</P>
<P>
PNA President Yasser Arafat is holding the consultations as
part of his preparation for the reshuffle of his PNA cabinet,
following strong criticism by the Palestinian Legislative Council
for corruption and mismanagement.
</P>
<P>
The parties that participated in the political dialog also
include the leading militant group Hamas, or Islamic Resistance
Movement, the Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine, the
Democratic Front of the Liberation of Palestine and the People
Party.
</P>
<P>
Despite the Arafat-led Palestine Liberation Organization
recognized Israel and began the current peace process since 1993,
Hamas and Islamic Jihad have refused to join the process and have
vowed to destroy Israel in order to establish an Islamic state.
</P>
<P>
The two groups have gained fame in the past years through
launching attacks against Israel, killing hundreds of Israelis in
a series of suicide bombings of Israeli buses and markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
