<HEADLINE> Iran's Official Calls for Establishment of Nuclear </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The nuclear tests in South Asia
underscores the necessity of establishment of a zone free from
nuclear and other weapons of mass destruction in the Middle East,
said an Iranian official here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In a speech to the Conference on Disarmament, Iran's deputy
foreign minister Javad Zarif called on the international community
to "exert every pressure on Israel to immediately abandon and
dismantle its nuclear weapon programs".
</P>
<P>
"Un-safeguarded nuclear facilities and clandestine nuclear
programs of Israel pose an imminent threat to the peace and
security of the region," Zarif said.
</P>
<P>
"A mistake should not be repeated twice," Zarif said, referring
to the nuclear tests by India and then by Pakistan last month.
</P>
<P>
"Anything less would but encourage Israel to continue enhancing
its nuclear arsenal, which will undoubtedly have grave
consequences for regional and global peace and security," he
warned.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian official urged Israel to accede without any
precondition to the Non-Proliferation Treaty (NPT) and accept
unconditionally the safeguards system of the Vienna-based
International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA).  
</P>
</TEXT>
