<HEADLINE> Plavsic: Bosnia a Lesson for Parties in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Bosnian Serb President
Biljana Plavsic said Thursday that the Bosnian war should be a
patent lesson to the parties involved in the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
After meeting Greek Foreign Minister Theodoros Pangalos,
Plavsic said that hostilities and clashes between the parties in
Kosovo must come to an end and individual rights and democratic
freedoms had to be guaranteed.
</P>
<P>
Violence in Kosovo, a province of the Federal Republic of
Yugoslavia, has been escalating due to ethnic Albanian's demand
for independence.
</P>
<P>
Plavsic and Pangalos agreed to make efforts to maintain peace
in the Balkan region and in Kosovo where ethnic Albanians comprise
90 percent of the province's nearly two million population.
</P>
<P>
The two also discussed the situation in Bosnia, the
implementation of the Dayton peace agreements and bilateral
relations.
</P>
<P>
Plavsic arrived in Greece on Monday at the invitation of the
non-governmental organization, Greek Solidarity Caravan, which
undertakes humanitarian missions to crisis areas and has been very
active in sending economic assistance to orphans of the war in
Bosnia. 
</P>
