stabilize the financial markets, the payment of wages to public
workers, the coal industry, and the upcoming cabinet session.
</P>
<P>
On the anti-crisis program announced by the premier in St.
Petersburg on Wednesday, Yeltsin said shortly before meeting with
Kiriyenko that the main component was "a clear system of control
over its implementation."
</P>
<P>
He said the program would be approved at a cabinet session on
June 23, which he will attend. 
