<HEADLINE> New Compaq Plans Integrated Greater China Division </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 18 (Xinhua) -- To achieve Compaq Computer's
vision of being the world's best computer company, Compaq Greater
China will integrate the main business of Compaq, Digital and
Tandem to offer the best technologies to customers, it was
announced here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Philip H. Yu, the newly-named president of the Division, with
his headquarters in Beijing, said that the organization and
management teams would be in place by July while the
implementation of policies and processes was expected in the three
months to come.
</P>
<P>
The restructuring of the company aimed at enhancing business
growth and integrating products, solutions and services from all
the three companies for the benefit of the customers, Yu said.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the restructuring was for Compaq Greater China to
increase its revenue to 1.5 billion to 2.0 billion U.S. dollars by
the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Compaq will be the company's master brand. Compaq Greater
China will help its channels and customers to manage a smooth
transition to the single brand while the existing brands "Digital"
and "Tandem" will continue to be used for some products, according
to Yu.
</P>
<P>
For computer and related services, China stands as a giant
market with very positive prospects. Confronted with heated
competition from the China-made products, Compaq, while promoting
for its own products and considering co-branding with Chinese
firms, will focus its efforts on offering quality support services
to customers.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1982, Compaq Computer Corporation is the world's
largest computer manufacturer and the largest global supplier of
personal computers. Its acquisition of Microcom Inc., Tandem
Computers Inc. and Digital Equipment Corporation were completed in
July and August last year and early this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
