<HEADLINE> Gifts From China's Mainland Attract Hong Kong Viewers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The official gifts from the
inland area, now on display to mark the first anniversary of Hong
Kong's return to China, have grasped the interest of more than
10,000 visitors over the last few days, the organizer said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
An average of 2,300 Hong Kong people toured the "More than
Gifts" exhibition daily, making it the most popular show ever
organized by the Provisional Regional Council.
