A Council spokesman attributed the enthusiastic response to
the public anxiety to view these precious items and to feel the
passion and blessing from the mainland.
</P>
<P>
The 16 gifts on display are selected from the full collection
presented to the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) by
the Central People's government, 31 provinces, autonomous regions
and municipalities in July last year.
</P>
<P>
The gifts, including cloisonne vases, porcelain vases,
ink-slabs, and tapestry which are gems of contemporary Chinese
art, convey blessings and wishes from the mainland. 
</P>
