<HEADLINE> More Law Schools At Chinese Universities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- There are law schools at more than
300 Chinese institutes of higher education, with 60,000 students
studying in the field at present, according to Zeng Xianyi, who is
in charge of legal studies at Chinese universities.
</P>
<P>
Zeng told a Sino-U.S. conference of law school heads that
People's University established the country's first law school in
1950.
</P>
<P>
The system now includes law schools, professional training, and
adult education, and has provided an education for 100,000
students and trained a million professionals.
</P>
<P>
Forty-three law schools can grant master's degrees, 8 can grant
doctor's degrees, and 8 have post-doc education centers.
</P>
<P>
According to Zeng, the number of law school students will
increase from the existing 2.2 percent of the total college
students to 3 percent by the year 2000 and to 4.5 percent by
2010. 
</P>
</TEXT>
