<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Falls 108 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, JUNE 18 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Thursday closed at 3292.33 as
against Wednesday's close of 3400.95, showing a fall of 108.62
points.
</P>
<P>
The national index also dipped by 45.18 points to 1438.04 from
the previous close of 1483.22.
</P>
<P>
Equities lost part of Wednesday's gains with the sensitive
index falling by over 109 points on the stock market Thursday in
the wake of heavy selling pressure by foreign institutional
investors and due to lack of aggressive support from financial
institutions. 
</P>
