<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Grants 1.5 Million ECU Aid for Kosovo Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission approved
on Thursday an emergency aid package of 1.5 million ECU (1.65
million U.S. dollars) for refugees fleeing Kosovo and for host
communities in neighboring Albania.
</P>
<P>
The package, to be managed by the European Community
Humanitarian Office, will enable United Nations institutions and
non-governmental organizations to deliver aid in the next three
months.
</P>
<P>
The funding will be used to help distribute the essentials,
such as food and medicine, to refugees and to host communities as
well as to reception centers which are preparing to accept more
refugees.
</P>
<P>
A total of 50,000 people are estimated to have fled their homes
in Kosovo and more than 10,000 have crossed the border into
Albania.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers of the 15-nation European Union decided
early last week to impose new sanctions on the Federal Republic of
Yugoslavia in an effort to force it to stop the indiscriminate use
of force against the civilian population in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The new sanctions include a ban on all new European investment
in Serbia and the freezing of Belgrade's state-held funds in EU
member countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
