<HEADLINE> Albania Protests Yugoslavia's Border Violation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The Albanian government protested
on Wednesday against an alleged Yugoslavian military violation of
the border between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
According to the Albanian Telegraphic Agency, Yugoslavian
frontier guards shot dead an Albanian who was on Albanian
territory on Tuesday, then crossed the border to pull the body
across to Yugoslavian soil.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to Belgrade's charge d'affaires ad interim to
Tirana, the Albanian Foreign Ministry warned that the dangerous
incident constituted an escalation of the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian government strongly urged Belgrade to stop
immediately violations which could lead to serious consequences,
the letter said.
</P>
<P>
On an inspection to the Albania-Yugoslavia border Wednesday,
Albanian President Rexhep Mejdani said his country was determined
to protect its boundary.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time Tirana has officially acknowledged border
clashes with Yugoslavia since the Serbian province of Kosovo
descended into a bloody military conflict in February.
</P>
<P>
Ethnic Albanians make up 90 percent of the population in the
province and separatists are seeking independence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
