<HEADLINE> FIFA Says England no Chance for 2002 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- International soccer body FIFA said here
on Thursday that it would be impossible for England to step in as
hosts even if Japan and South Korea could not host the 2002 World Cup
finals.
</P>
<P>
FIFA spokesman Keith Cooper said, "There were reports in the
British press that England might step in. I would say for many many
reasons this is completely excluded."
</P>
<P>
England is bidding for the 2006 World Cup along with Germany but
the British media had discussed the possibility of England replacing
co-hosts Japan and South Korea for the 2002 edition if Asia was hit a
financial crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
