<HEADLINE> FIFA: No Threat of Withdrawl from Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- International soccer body FIFA said here
on Thursday that Iran has never threatened to withdraw from the
ongoing World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
FIFA spokesman Keith Cooper said the Iranian Football Association
had lodged a formal protest to FIFA but there had been no mention for
a boycott of later games.
</P>
<P>
The Iranians were outraged by the "totally untrue and false"
depiction of their home country in a movie shown by a French
television station.
</P>
<P>
Iran will meet the United States in group F in Lyon on Sunday,
which coincides with FIFA's Fair Play Day. 
</P>
