<HEADLINE> Paris to Strictly Regulate Sale of Alcohol during World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Paris will strictly regulate the
sale of alcohol during what remains of the World Cup finals, said
Paris Police Chief Philippe Massoni on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He made the announcement hours before the match Thursday
evening between France and Saudi Arabia at the Stadium of France
in Saint-Denis outside Paris.
</P>
<P>
Massoni said that alcohol drinking will also be banned around
the five giant screens to transmit live the game.
</P>
<P>
But no extra time restriction will be imposed on shops selling
alcohol.
</P>
<P>
Paris will host a Music Festival from Sunday to Morning and
will organize a festival on the final day of the World Cup on July
12, two days prior to the French National Day celebration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
