<HEADLINE> Montpellier to Restrict Music Festival Celebration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The southern French city of
Montpellier will restrict the time for celebration during the
Music Festival to be held from Sunday to Monday, said the local
governor of the Herault region Daniel Constantin on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
All celebrations should be stopped and bars closed before two
o'clock in the morning, because of a large presence of Tunisian
fans in the city for the match between Tunisia and Colombia on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,500 Tunisian fans are expected to come down to the city
for the game to be held at the Mosson Stadium of the city.
</P>
<P>
The nearby city of Toulouse has cancelled the Music Festival
because of a game between England and Romania on the same day
there.
</P>
<P>
All French cities hosting the World Cup finals are scared by
the hooliganism of English and Tunisian fans in Marseille early
this week. 
</P>
