<HEADLINE> Mongolia Grants Visa-Free Access for HKSAR Passport Holders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The government of Mongolia has
granted visa-free access for a period of up to 14 days for holders
of Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) passports, an
SAR government spokesman said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
An agreement for mutual exemption of visa requirement between
Mongolia and Hong Kong was signed Thursday by Mongolian Ambassador
to the People's Republic of China Dagva Tsakhilgaan and Director
of Immigration of the HKSAR Regina Ip.
</P>
<P>
"We welcome the decision which signifies the confidence of the
government of Mongolia in Hong Kong and the HKSAR passport," the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Mongolian nationals will likewise enjoy 14
days' visa-free visit to Hong Kong. 
