<HEADLINE> 12 Injured in Bomb Explosions in Karachi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 18 (Xinhua) -- At least 12 people were injured
when two bombs went off Thursday afternoon at two separate places
in Karachi, a southern port city of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The Associated Press of Pakistan (APP) said five people were
injured in a bomb explosion that occurred just outside the gate of
Tughlaq House where government offices of Sindh Province are
located.
</P>
<P>
The APP quoted police sources as saying that the explosive
device was planted on a motorcycle which went off at around 12.40
p.m.
</P>
<P>
The motorcycle on which the device was planted and two cars
parked close to it were damaged.
</P>
<P>
The blast was the second in the city in a span of just 30
minutes.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, an explosive device also planted on a motorcycle went
off just outside the main entrance of Karachi Stock Exchange
(KSE), wounding at least seven people.
</P>
<P>
The APP said that the explosions appeared to have been aimed at
creating panic among people.
</P>
<P>
The KSE-100 Index, which surged by 18 points in the morning
session, suddenly plunged by 17 points after the blasts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
