<HEADLINE> Photo Show Opens in Macao to Commemorate Zhou Enlai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 18 (Xinhua) -- A photo exhibition opened here
Thursday to commemorate the centenary of the birth of China's late
Premier Zhou Enlai.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, which attracted large numbers of visitors in
Beijing and Hong Kong, displays more than 200 pictures and
daily-use articles once used by the late premier, who died in
January 1976.
</P>
<P>
In particular, there are several pictures showing Zhou being
with well-known compatriots from Hong Kong and Macao.
</P>
<P>
Lee Shing Chun, director of the Macao Daily News, which
co-organized the exhibition, praised Zhou as an outstanding leader
of the Communist Party of China and of the People's Republic of
China as well as a main founder of the People's Liberation Army.
</P>
<P>
He said Zhou is remembered by the people in Macao because he
had shown special concern for Macao residents. The late premier
had instructed Guangdong provincial leaders to build a reservoir
to supply drinking water to Macao.
</P>
<P>
"The exhibition will help us know more about him and China's
contemporary history," he said in a speech at the opening
ceremony. "It will also help increase people's confidence in the
policy of 'one country, two systems' and Macao's better future."
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will last until June 21. 
</P>
