<HEADLINE> China's Chemicals Production Rebounds in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- China's chemical industry
rebounded with a 5 percent increase in output value in May on a
monthly basis, according to statistics from the State Petroleum
and Chemical Industry Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The output value was also up 7.3 percent compared with the
corresponding period of last year to 25.97 billion yuan, based on
the constant price in 1990, the figures show.
</P>
<P>
A bureau official said the industry is gaining momentum with
the macro-economy becoming stronger as it entered the second
quarter.
</P>
<P>
The sector produced an output value of 117 billion yuan in
the first five months of this year, accounting for 39 percent of
the objective for this year.
</P>
<P>
The figures show that the production of 12 of the 16 major
chemical products is higher than the previous month.
</P>
<P>
In May, the output of fertilizers increased to 2.39 million
tons, while the inventory of petite fertilizers dropped to 4.95
million tons, down 25.5 percent from the corresponding period of
last year.
</P>
<P>
China turned out 39,000 tons of pesticides in May and the
five-month total was 172,000 tons, representing 61.4 percent of
the projected annual production. 
</P>
</TEXT>
