to hit a new high this year.
</P>
<P>
In April, German imports rose by 12.9 percent to 72 billion
marks (40.4 billion dollars), leaving trade surplus at 11.4
billion marks (6.4 billion dollars), compared with 9.6 billion
marks (5.4 billion dollars) a year before.
</P>
<P>
From January to April, German exports increased by 15.3 percent
to a record 318.2 billion marks (178.6 billion dollars), while
imports reached 276.1 billion marks (154.9 billion dollars), up
12.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Germany's trade surplus was 42.1 billion marks (23.6 billion
dollars) for the first four months, compared with 31.7 billion
marks (17.8 billion dollars) during the same period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The office reported that the country's four-month current
accounts -- the sum of visible trade, services and transfers --
showed a deficit of 3.9 billion marks (2.2 billion dollars)
despite a surplus of 2.4 billion marks (1.3 billion dollars)
registered in April.
</P>
<P>
But the four-month balance was improved considering the 7.3
billion marks (4.1 billion dollars) deficit during the same period
of 1997, according to the office. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
