<HEADLINE> England Referee Critizes World Cup Refereeing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- A top English Premiership referee
critized his counterparts at the World Cup finals, saying they
failed to protect the skilful players.
</P>
<P>
David Elleray, one of the best referee in the Premiership
League, said:"The sad fact is that the first week (of the World Cup
finals) has been notable for increasingly weak officiating that has
failed to protect the skilful players and promote attacking play."
</P>
<P>
"Since the Italy-Chile match, the overall standard of refereeing
has gone steadily down," said Elleray.
</P>
<P>
Elleray said:"Many outrageous tackles and offences that should
have had yellow cards have gone unpunished."
</P>
<P>
FIFA president Sepp Blatter and French Organising Committee
President Michael Platini had already critized the refereeing of the
World Cup finals earlier on Wednesday. 
</P>
