<HEADLINE> Shaanxi Province Reinforces Key Construction Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Shaanxi Province
is engaged in extensive efforts to strengthen a series of key
construction projects.
</P>
<P>
The list of projects includes harnessing the loess plateau,
constructing the state-level Yangling High-Tech Agriculture Zone,
and completing the Xi'an-Ankang, Shenmu-Yan'an and Xi'an-Nanjing
railways.
</P>
<P>
Li Jianguo, secretary of the Shaanxi Committee of the Communist
Party of China, noted that efforts will not only include improving
the railway and highway networks, but also increasing the handling
capacity for the Xianyang International Airport and developing
water, electricity, gas and heat supply systems.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi, a province with abundant energy resources, will
expedite work at the Baoji No.2 Power Plant, as well as six other
power plants. Development continues on large coal mines such as
Shenfu, Huangling and Yushen.
</P>
<P>
Plans for the year 2000 call for Shaanxi to have a coal
production capacity of 74 million tons, total generating capacity
of 9.3 million kw, crude oil production capacity of five million
tons, refining capacity of six million tons and annual gas
production capacity of five billion cubic meters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
