<HEADLINE> Northeast Asia Trade Cooperation Zone Established in Harbin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 18 (Xinhua) -- A northeast Asia trade and
technology cooperation zone was set up recently in Harbin, capital
of Heilongjiang Province.
</P>
<P>
Approved by the Heilongjiang provincial government, the zone
covers 16 square kilometers of land equipped with complete
infrastructure facilities.
</P>
<P>
About 145 enterprises entered the zone, 38 of which are
overseas-funded. These enterprises have an annual gross domestic
product of 2 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Directed by the international market with high-tech as its main
target, the zone is engaged in economic technology cooperation,
export processing, and reciprocal trade.
</P>
<P>
The zone will develop into an export product-processing base to
Russia, provide information consultation services for Sino-Russia
trade cooperation, and introduce talents and technology from
Russia and northeast Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
A series of preferential policies is being given to the zone by
the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation to utilize
foreign investment with the right to conduct foreign trade and to
give quota licenses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
