<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Newspaper Editor's Residence Attacked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The residence of Lasantha
Wickrematunga, editor of the Sri Lankan newspaper Sunday Leader,
was attacked Wednesday night by an unidentified gang wielding T-56
weapons, a government spokesman said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Wickrematunga's residence is located at Kamdewatte Road,
Nugegoda in Western Province, about 30 kilometers from Colombo.
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred at around 11:00 last night, five minutes
after Wickrematunga returned home, Spokesman Mangala Samaraweera
said at a press conference.
</P>
<P>
Wickrematunga was not hurt but his house and two motor vehicles
have been damaged. T-56 firearms were used in the attack and
police who arrived at the scene minutes later recovered 26 empty
shells in the vicinity.
</P>
<P>
The gang had escaped in a white van after their attack.
</P>
<P>
A special police team has been deployed to arrest the culprits.
investigations are under way, the spokesman added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
