<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, June 18 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic, apparently
happy with the result of his talks with his Russian counterpart
Boris Yeltsin, left Moscow for home Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
During the talks with Yeltsin on Tuesday, Milosevic promised to
resume negotiations with leaders of ethnic Albanians in the Kosovo
region. The two sides also released a joint statement concerning
various issues in Kosovo, including possible forms of autonomy
for the area, the Itar-Tass news agency report.
(Russia-Yugoslavia-Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Argentine President Carlos Menem will visit
Britain on October 27 to November 1. He is the first Argentine
president to visit Britain since 1982 when the two countries were
engaged in a war, the Argentine Foreign Ministry announced
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Argentine Foreign Minister Guido di Tella said Wednesday that
Menem's visit is to help establish mutual trust between the two
nations, because mutual acceptance between them needs to be
improved. (Argentina-Britain-Visit)
</P>
