- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Proposed legislation to curb teenager smoking and
bring nicotine under federal regulation died in the Republican
controlled Senate of the United States Congress on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Following a four-week struggle on the Senate floor, supporters
of the bill failed on two successive procedural votes to gain the
60 votes needed to keep the bill alive. (US-Tobacco-Bill)
</P>
