</P>
<P>
NEW YORK -- U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright said
Wednesday that it is time to test the possibilities for bridging
the gap between the U.S. and Iran despite the fact that the gap
"remains wide."
</P>
<P>
"We are ready to explore further ways to build mutual
confidence and avoid misunderstanding," Albright said at an Asia
Society function in New York. She, who urged Iran to "consider
parallel steps," also praised Iran for its efforts in bringing
peace in Afghanistan, its achievements in anti-drug combat and its
aid to Iraqi and Afghan refugees. (US-Iran-Relations)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
VIENNA -- The current chairman of the Organization for Security
and Cooperation in Europe, Poland's Foreign Minister Bronislaw
Geremek, said here Wednesday that Yugoslavia's territorial
integrity brooks no infringement.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference, Geremek said that the conflict
in the troubled Kosovo province of Yugoslavia is a "test for
Europe." He warned those "tension-makers" among ethnic Albanians
that Yugoslav territorial integrity brooks no infringement.
(OSCE-Kosovo)
</P>
