<HEADLINE> Three Players Get One-Match Suspensions by FIFA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The world governing FIFA has decided to
suspend three players from their next match for having received a
second yellow card in the World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
The players are Cesar Sampaio from the Brazilian team, Said
Chiba from Morocco and Darren Jackson from Scotland.
</P>
<P>
FIFA has already decided to give Dutch star Patrick Kluivert a
two-match ban as he received a red card for elbowing his Belgian
opponent. 
</P>
