<DOCNO> XIE19980618.0233 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Govt Proposes New Minimum Wage in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania has set up a board
which is responsible for proposing new minimum wage in private
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Mateo Qaresi, the Minister of State for Central Establishment,
said members of the board are reviewing the existing minimum wage
scales in the private sector before coming out with proposals.
</P>
<P>
Presently, the statutory minimum wage for the private sector
is 17,500 shillings (about 26 U.S. Dollars).
</P>
<P>
Qaresi said the members of the board, appointed by the Labor
Ministry, will take into consideration the costs of basic needs,
economic situation and employees' financial position, media
reports said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The proposals will later be presented to the president for
approval before they are released for implementation, the
minister said Wednesday at a parliamentary session in Dodoma, a
city in central Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
He said the government will raise salaries of its employees to
enable them to meet the rising costs of living when the economic
situation turns for the better.
</P>
<P>
The government is aware that the salaries have not been
sufficient for employees, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
