<HEADLINE> Heavy Rain Soaks Chinese Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- A heavy rainstorm hit the Chinese
capital this afternoon accompanied by strong wind and hail.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the Beijing Municipal Meteorological Station said
that the rainstorm and hail were caused by strong heat convection
in some areas.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the rainstorm and hail mainly hit areas
between Xuanwumen and Muxidi, some six kilometers to the west of
Tian'anmen Square in downtown Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Lin Bing, an official from the North China Air Traffic Control
Bureau's Meteorological Service Center, said the rainstorm had no
effect on flights at Capital International Airport.
</P>
<P>
The official said they are paying close attention to the
climatic changes and will react immediately to guarantee safe
flights.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, no reports of rain had come from Beijing suburban
districts or counties.  
</P>
</TEXT>
