<HEADLINE> U.S. Company Unveils New Supercomputer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Silicon Graphics, a leading
U.S. computer workstation maker, unveiled a new supercomputer that
is twice as fast as its current models, the company said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"This is a breakthrough product providing customers with
leading, cost-effective performance," said Bill Minto, director of
product management at Silicon Graphics.
</P>
<P>
The new supercomputer, called Cray SV1, is the first in a
series of products which have a peak performance of four billion
calculations a second, the company claimed.
</P>
<P>
The California-based Silicon Graphics makes computers with
advanced graphics capabilities that have a range of uses from
simulated nuclear testing to the design of special effects for
movies.
</P>
<P>
Minto said the new supercomputer is due to be available in the
United States in August at a list price of 500,000 U.S. dollars
and his company already has a backlog of 20 million dollars in
orders for the new machine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
