<HEADLINE> NBA SuperSonics Name New Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Seattle SuperSonics president
Wally Walker has decided to make Paul Westphal the team's head
coach, according to news reports here.
</P>
<P>
But team officials today would not confirm the reports, saying
they probably would have some kind of announcement later.
</P>
<P>
Westphal's pending deal to replace George Karl was reported by
Seattle radio station.
</P>
<P>
Walker and Westphal, a former Phoenix Suns coach, are close to
agreement on a two-or three-year deal worth between one million
U.S. dollars and 1.5 million dollars per season, accoridng to the
report.
</P>
<P>
Walker refused to commment on the decision. Westphal, 47, beat
out Bob Hill, Charlotte Hornets assistant Paul Silas and former
Sonics assistant Bob Weiss for the job.
</P>
<P>
The Sonics waited until after the NBA Finals so they could
speak to Chicago Bulls coach Phil Jackson, but Walker changed his
mind after hearing that Jackson needed more time to decide his
future.
</P>
<P>
Westphal led the Suns to the 1993 NBA Finals in his first
season as coach, but was fired during the 1995-1996 season. In
three-plus seasons at Phoenix, he had a 191-88 record. 
</P>
