<HEADLINE> World Bank Grants for China's Sustainable Development Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANTAI, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank is expected to
provide 4.57 million US dollars for a coastal sustainable growth
project in Rongcheng, a city in east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The international financial institution has just completed
evaluation of the project and signed a loaning agreement. The
loans will have a term of 20 years.
</P>
<P>
The Rongcheng project is part of a large project in
comprehensive development of marine resources in southeast China's
coastal areas designed by China's Ministry of Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank-funded project, which will be launched next year
and completed in three years, covers breeding and fish and oyster
raising and the processing of aquatic products.
</P>
<P>
After completion of the project, it can produce two million
heads of fry, 15 million tons of grown-up fish, 6,000 tons of
oysters, and 3,400 tons of processed aquatic products, with sales
income totaling 243 million yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
