<HEADLINE> Minister Predicts China's Long-term Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, June 18 (Xinhua) -- China is able to maintain sustained
and rapid economic growth in a fairly long period of time, a
senior official said.
</P>
<P>
China now enjoys unprecedented opportunities and advantages in
realizing sustained and rapid economic growth, Zeng Peiyan,
minister of the State Development Planning Commission, said at an
international seminar of "China Marching Toward 2020" held here
recently.
</P>
<P>
The opportunities favorable for China's economic growth include
trend of world peace and development, accelerating national
industrial restructuring, the rapid development of high and new
technology, and the burgeoning of a knowledge-based economy, he
told the seminar.
</P>
<P>
China's overall national strength will be even more greater by
the end of this century and the changes in the economic system and
economic operations will facilitate economic growth in a long
period of time, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that improvement in infrastructure has bolstered
China's economic growth potential and enabled China to make better
use of domestic and overseas markets and resources.
</P>
<P>
In addition, China has great market potential in urban housing
and transport and in the wide rural areas, Zeng said. He added
that China's sustained and rapid economic growth in the years
ahead will be of significant importance to global economic
progress.
</P>
<P>
He estimated China's imports in the first five years of the
next century at around one trillion US dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
