<HEADLINE> Second Girl Rescued from Cave Dies of Heart Failure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The second of two girls who had
been trapped for 42 days in a cave in southwestern China's Guizhou
Province died here Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
Li Qingzhu, 16, died of heart failure.
</P>
<P>
Liang Xiaofei, 19, Li's classmate, died two days earlier.
</P>
<P>
A doctor in charge of her medical treatment, said Li suffered
from acidosis and a lung infection since her rescue on June 13,
together with Liang.
</P>
<P>
The hospital was unable to save the extremely weak girl despite
extensive medical efforts.
</P>
<P>
However, the doctor said, "it is a miracle that the two girls
had survived 42 days without any food."
</P>
<P>
A party of four explorers stumbled on the girls, and found that
their companions, Huang Yan and Wang Shunrong, had already died of
starvation.
</P>
<P>
The four entered the cave on May 2 without informing anyone of
their whereabouts and got lost when their candles were
extinguished.
</P>
<P>
Their schools reported them missing on May 9. 
</P>
</TEXT>
