<HEADLINE> Thai Property Owners Eye U.S. Buyers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 18 (Xinhua) -- With limited purchasing power at
home, Thai real-estate businessmen are eyeing the other side of
the Pacific Ocean, hoping a second housing roadshow could lure
more U.S. buyers.
</P>
<P>
ERA (Thailand) Co., the country's largest real-estate franchise
broker, plans a second housing roadshow in the United States on
August 1-17, the Bangkok Post said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The roadshow aims to encourage Thai business people living in
the United States to invest in their home country and to attract
those wanting to own a second home in Thailand, the newspaper
said.
</P>
<P>
The show will be held in the Thai communities in New York,
Chicago and Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
A similar event in April, held in Los Angeles, Chicago and
Washington, generated 150 million baht (3.6 million U.S. dollars)
in residential and industrial property sales.
</P>
<P>
The August exhibition will be divided into three parts:
residential and industrial projects, golf courses, and franchise
business opportunities.
</P>
<P>
About 15 local property developers are expected to join the
trip, and 30 golf courses are interested in having ERA organize a
display to showcase their properties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
