<HEADLINE> Thailand's Car Imports Up in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Imports of passenger cars rose
sharply in May compared with April, but were still far below the
level a year ago, the Bangkok Post Thursday quoted the Customs
Department as saying.
</P>
<P>
A total of 507 cars were imported in May, down by 1,203 units
or 70.35 percent from the same month last year, but up 471 units
or 1,308 percent from April.
</P>
<P>
Of the 507 cars, 479 came from Europe, 25 from Japan, two from
South Korea and one from the United States.
</P>
<P>
The most popular brand among imported cars is Volkswagen, 402
units, followed by Audi, 68 units, Toyota, 25 units, and BMW and
Mercedes Benz.
</P>
<P>
The Customs Department collected 359.16 million baht (8.6
million U.S. dollars) in import duties from cars in May, down by
59.36 percent from May 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
