<HEADLINE> Dhaka to Receive Japan's Grant for Debt Relief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will receive 70 million
U.S. dollars from Japan as grant for its debt relief under an
agreement, press reports said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Japan would provide Bangladesh with a grant assistance of the
said amount with the intention of producing the same effect as
canceling an international debt, said the exchange of notes signed
between the two sides in Dhaka Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The grant would enable the recipient country to purchase
commodities and equipment from all member countries of the
Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development, the notes
stated.
</P>
<P>
Since the grant was to be utilized by the Bangladeshi
government for the import of commodities and equipment for
much-needed investment programs, it would substantially contribute
to development in various sectors of the Bangladeshi economy and
social welfare, it said.
</P>
<P>
It would also contribute considerably to improving the balance
of payment position of the recipient country, it added. 
</P>
