<HEADLINE> Albright Urges Dialogue Between Albanians and Belgrade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 18 (Xinhua) - United States Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright has urged Kosovo Albanians to dialogue with
Belgrade in an effort to solve the current crisis peacefully.
</P>
<P>
Constructive dialogue is the only way the crisis can be solved
politically and permanently, Albright said in a letter Wednesday
to Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano. She hoped that Albania
would deliver this message to Kosovo's Albanians.
</P>
<P>
She praised Albania's commitment to backing the efforts of
Kosovo's Albanian leaders to solve the crisis peacefully. The
U.S. government is studying ways to deal with the rapidly
deteriorating situation, and to provide Albania with the best
assistance possible, Albright said.
</P>
<P>
Belgrade must end the violence against Kosovo Albanians that is
endangering the dialogue process, Albright said in the letter.
</P>
<P>
A U.S. envoy to the region said during a telephone call to
Nano the same day that military intervention is still a
U.S. government alternative on ending the crisis swiftly and
permanently. 
</P>
