<HEADLINE> Ecuadoran Oil Price Continues to Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The prices of Ecuadoran crude
dropped from 11 to 7.1 dollars per barrel this month, the lowest
level in recent years, the state-owned company Petroecuador said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
the company said the worldwide oversupply of oil continues and
Monday's petroleum prices were down to their lowest rate in the
past 12 years.
</P>
<P>
Three of the six members of the Gulf Cooperation Council
decided in Riyadh, capital of Saudi Arabia, Tuesday to cut their
oil production by 170,000 barrels daily, beginning from July 1 to
stop the fall in the oil price.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia, the world's top oil producer and exporter, agreed
with Mexico and Venezuela to cut their output respectively by
450,000 barrels per day at the beginning of the month. 
