<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Some 60 elephants have gone on a
rampage recently in Aceh in the northern part of Indonesia's
Sumatra, damaging villages and farms, Antara News Agency reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
People from two districts have expressed concern over the
elephant attacks which could happen day or night and what these
could cause on their farms.
</P>
<P>
