<HEADLINE> Tamils in Canada Fund Sri Lanka's Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Tamil groups in Canada
particularly in the Toronto area are funding Sri Lanka's rebel
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE), according to reports
reaching here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
They are sending over one million U.S. dollars a month to buy
arms and weapons for the LTTE to fight the Sri Lankan government.
</P>
<P>
The funds are reportedly being collected by two groups through
threats, extortion, fraud and drug dealing from the 150,000 Sri
Lankan Tamils living in Toronto.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka's High Commissioner to Canada Ananda Gunasekera has
been quoted as saying that the Sri Lankan government has been
urging the Canadian government to bar these groups from raising
funds.
</P>
<P>
He said the money collected there is causing a lot of damage in
Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
The Federation of Associations of Canadian Tamils (FACT), an
umbrella organization comprising ten Tamil groups in Canada, has
been identified by the U.S. State department as one of the front
organizations of the LTTE.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka's Foreign Minister Lakshman Kadirgamar has recently
said that the bombing of Sri Lanka's Central Bank in January 1996
was funded by money raised in Canada.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan government believes that the LTTE is raising
funds worldwide posing as religious, cultural, social, educational
and humanitarian bodies.
</P>
<P>
In the recent past, India, Malaysia and the U.S. have taken
steps to control activities of LTTE front organizations, the
reports added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
