<HEADLINE> Peru: Small, Micro-Companies' Contribution to GDP Grows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The share of output by Small and
Micro-Companies of Peru (PYME) in the Gross Domestic Product (GDP)
amounts to 45 percent and will grow to 46 percent within the year.
</P>
<P>
The figure was between 35 and 37 percent seven years ago, said
Francisco Martinotti, executive director of the commission for the
PYME's promotion, in an interview with the media here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Though big companies' production and profits were larger, the
contribution of the PYME had been growing over the past years,
said Martinotti.
</P>
<P>
Peru has three million units of PYMEs, which represent 98
percent of the productive sector of Peru, Martinotti said.
</P>
