<HEADLINE> Serbia Backs Yeltsin-Milosevic Statement on Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The Serbian government Wednesday
showed its support for the joint statement by Russian President
Boris Yeltsin and Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic on solving
the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
An announcement issued by the Serbian Information Ministry said
the government had decided to take concrete measures to fulfil the
tasks set by the joint statement.
</P>
<P>
Milosevic, who is under threat of NATO military action to call
off the Serb crackdown on ethnic Albanian separatists, held talks
with Yeltsin in Moscow on Tuesday and gave some guarantees in the
joint statement.
</P>
<P>
The announcement said relevant departments were instructed to
take all means to ensure the free passage of Kosovo people in the
province and ensure the safety of their lives and properties.
</P>
<P>
The government would also help people who fled from their
residences to return home and rebuild their houses which, the
statement said, had been ruined by terrorists in the riots.
</P>
<P>
The government would cooperate with the International Committee
of the Red Cross and the United Nations High Commissioner for
Refugees on the return and settlement of the displaced. 
</P>
