<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thousands of Peruvians Infected With AIDS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, June 17 (Xinhua) -- About 7,000 to 10,000 Peruvians were
found to have been infected with AIDS as of April and 70,000
others were identified as HIV carriers, the Peru Ministry of
Health said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At least one thousand new cases of the disease are registered
in the country every year and the number seems to continue to
increase incrementally to 1,200, and then to 1,400, said doctor
Pedro Mendoza, who is responsible for the support services program
in the ministry.
</P>
<P>
Since the first case of AIDS was reported in the country in
1983, 250 million U.S. dollars have been spent in Peru on the
disease, Mendoza said.
</P>
<P>
He said that in the past few years, the Peruvian government has
increased the budget by 400 percent for the AIDS control program.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
