<HEADLINE> Ten Ethnic Albanians Killed in Fresh Yugoslav Border Fights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav border guards shot dead
10 ethnic Albanians as they were trying to enter Kosovo illegally
from Albania, Pristina news service said.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian deaths occurred in two separate gunfights Tuesday
and Wednesday, each involving five deaths. No casualties were
reported among the Yugoslav troops.
</P>
<P>
The Tanjug news agency reported that a Serb policeman on patrol
was seriously wounded in an Albanian attack in Crnoljev of Kosovo
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, a Yugoslav solider was killed as a group of
ethnic Albanians fired at a Yugoslav army barracks in the village
of Luznic in the troubled province of Kosovo. 
</P>
