<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ningbo Unveils New Rules to Woo Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, June 18 (Xinhua) -- This port city of east China's
Zhejiang Province has just unveiled a set of new rules to attract
more overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
Overseas companies are allowed and encouraged to invest in
productive projects, technical renovation projects and
export-oriented agricultural projects, according to the new rules.
</P>
<P>
Also welcome is overseas investment in new and high technology
and airport, port, highway, power, energy, water conservancy and
environmental protection projects.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investors in the above-mentioned areas will be exempt
from corporate income tax for different time periods and will get
partial or full tax refunds after the exemption periods complete.
</P>
<P>
The new rules also encourage overseas companies to invest in
scientific research, education, intermediary services and the
development of tourism facilities. They will also enjoy
preferential tax treatment.
</P>
<P>
As stipulated in the new rules, Ningbo will engage in
Sino-overseas cooperation in wholesale and retail business,
banking, insurance, tourism and foreign trade on a limited basis.
</P>
<P>
Investors in the local development and bonded zones will also
enjoy bottom land prices and receive priority treatment in the
supply of water, power and gas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980618.0320 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sichuan Attracts More Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Sichuan Province
experienced a hefty increase in overseas investment in the first
five months of this year.
</P>
<P>
Contracted overseas investment in Sichuan was valued at more
than 500 million US dollars in the first five months, up by 72
percent over the same period of last year. Overseas paid-in
investment soared 62 percent to more than 200 million US dollars
for the January-May period, according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
Persisting overseas investor confidence and increasing
investment in infrastructure and high-tech projects are a major
reason for surging overseas investment in Sichuan, experts pointed
out.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, many overseas-funded projects signed in the past
years are being implemented, resulting in a significant increase in
actual overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan leads many other provinces and regions in southwest
China in terms of economic development and the level of opening-up
to the rest of the world. The amount of overseas investment
utilized is the greatest in the less- developed central and
western areas.
</P>
<P>
To attract more overseas investment, Sichuan will unveil rules
and regulations on the development of mineral and water resources
later this year and will also cancel all unreasonable fees for
overseas-funded enterprises, according to Tang Limin, a
provincial government official. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980618.0321 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Weihai Development Zone Attracts More Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANTAI, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Despite the fallout of the
lingering Asian financial crisis, a development zone in east
China's Shandong Province has made successful attempts to attract
overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
The contracted value of overseas investment in the Weihai
Economic and Technological Development Zone surged 46.8 percent
year-on-year in the first five months of this year, with the value
of paid-in investment hitting 30 million US dollars, according to
official statistics.
</P>
<P>
Southeast Asia used to account for 90 percent of overseas
investment in Weihai, with a particular large part coming from the
Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
As the financial crisis has gulfed and continued to hurt many
Asian nations since last July, the zone has had to readjust its
measures to attract overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
A major effort in this regard is the introduction of national
treatment to overseas companies and overseas-funded enterprises,
under which all firms are equally treated in project approval, tax
and labor policies, housing, medical service, collection of
administrative charges, among other things.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the zone authorities have taken measures to improve
services for overseas investors and cooperate with related
departments, higher education institutions and research institutes
to attract overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
The zone has also made effective efforts to enhance cooperation
with overseas intermediary agencies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
