<HEADLINE> Kafelnikov Beaten in Dutch First Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Second seed Yevgeni Kafelnikov of
Russia crashed out of the 500,000 U.S. dollars Heineken Trophy
grass court tennis tournament in Den Bosch, Netherlands on
Wednesday, losing to Steve Campbell in the first round.
</P>
<P>
24-year-old Kafelnikov lost 7-5, 6-2 to his unfancied American
rival, ranked 99 in the world.
</P>
<P>
Top seed Australian Patrick Rafter needed three sets to defeat
Czech Daniel Vacek, 6-3, 4-6, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Sixth seeded Brazilian Gustavo Kuerten was knocked out 3-6,
6-4, 7-6 (7-2) by Dutch qualifier Dennis van Scheppingen.
</P>
<P>
In the first round of the women's action, third seed Dominique
van Roost of Belgium went down to Miriam Oremans of the
Netherlands 6-3, 7-6 and last year's winner Ruxandra Dragomir of
Romania was beaten 7-6 (7-4), 6-3 by Julie Halard-Decugis of
France.
</P>
<P>
In the second round, which was also held on Wednesday, top seed
Amanda Coetzer of South Africa lost 6-4, 6-2 to Kimberly Po of the
United States while second seed Sandrine Testud of France edged
Italian 6-3, 6-4. 
</P>
