Drought.
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin was interviewed by Elizabeth
G. Weymouth, special editor of U.S. Newsweek and concurrently
columnist of Washington Post, at Zhongnanhai, site of China's
Central Government, yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Jiang answered her questions on Sino-U.S. relations, the Taiwan
issue, China's entry to WTO, China's role in the Asian financial
crisis and the situation in South Asia.
</P>
<P>
-- A photo album on Chinese President Jiang Zemin's state
