<HEADLINE> Shanghai Ranks First in Mobile Phone Subscribers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 18 (Xinhua) -- By the end of May, eight out of
each 100 Shanghainese had become mobile phone subscribers, pushing
the total number of such customers to nearly one million, the
first among large cities in China.
</P>
<P>
The subscribers of the China Telecom in the city topped
870,000, while those of China Unicom surpassed 100,000, 16 percent
of the city's market shares.
</P>
<P>
While in its initial stage of development, the mobile phone
service in Shanghai mainly relied on two analogue networks. Now
the city has been equipped with the more advanced GSM, DCS and
CDMA facilities, enabling clearer and more stable communication.
</P>
</TEXT>
