<HEADLINE> New Ruling Party Formed in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President-elect Joseph
Estrada has formed a new party from the fractious three-party
coalition that helped him win last month's elections, the Manila
Times reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The report said Estrada announced Wednesday night the formation
of the new ruling party, the Laban ng Masang Filipino (Filipino
Masses Party), saying the merger was to save the coalition which
had appeared headed for a collapse after the elections.
</P>
<P>
Three main opposition parties formed the coalition early this
year and helped Estrada defeat House Speaker Jose de Venecia, the
standard bearer of the strong ruling party, in the May 11
elections.
</P>
<P>
Estrada will assume the presidency when President Fidel Ramos'
term ends on June 30. 
</P>
