<HEADLINE> Electrification of Harbin-Dalian Railway Line Under Way </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese workers have started to
work on electrifying Tieling-Anshan section of Harbin-Dalian
railway line in northeast China.
</P>
<P>
The electrification of the entire 946-km Harbin-Dalian railway
line will be carried out in three parts: Harbin-Tieling,
Tieling-Anshan, Anshan-Dalian sections, which will be constructed
by three separate companies.
</P>
<P>
Workers have been working on electrifying the Harbin-Tieling
section since May 18.
</P>
<P>
Xi'an Railway Engineering Corporation has given the task of
building the haulage and power facilities for an electrified
160-km Anshan-Tieling section, which is situated inside Liaoning
Province, said local sources. The project is listed as one of the
state's key construction projects for 1998.
</P>
<P>
The electrification of the entire Harbin-Dalian railway line is
scheduled to be completed and put into service by 2000. By then,
the railway line, the only electrification rail in northeast
China, will allow trains to pass at a speed of 140 km and will see
a rise of 5,000 tons in its haulage weight, said engineers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
