<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Establishes Lab on Weather Modification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, June 18 (Xinhua) -- China established first weather
modification lab in an artificial rainfall base in northeast
China's Jilin Province.
</P>
<P>
The lab is jointly run by National Meteorological Bureau and
Jinlin provincial government.
</P>
<P>
In the past years, China only has one institute of weather
modification. It is attached to Chinese Academy of Meteorology.
</P>
<P>
With rapid growth of the economic development, disasters caused
by bad weather as drought, hailstone and early frost brought about
heavier losses to crop growth.
</P>
<P>
Liu Shuying, deputy head of the lab, said China has achieved
great progress in weather modification since its launching of
first artificial rain on July 21, 1958 over the sky in Fengman
Reservoir in Jilin.
</P>
<P>
She said, only in Jinlin Province, more than 1,300 sorties of
planes took off for artificial rainfalls, which increased 20
percent of the rainfalls in the province in the past decades.
</P>
<P>
Liu said the lab is managing to become a state-level one with
two or three years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
