<HEADLINE> U.N. Chief to Continue Mediation in Cyprus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 17 (Xinhua) -- United Nations
Secretary-General Kofi Annan said he will continue making efforts
to resume negotiations between the leaders of the two communities
in Cyprus, his spokesman said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"In order to continue to explore possibilities that may lead to
a new momentum, my special adviser on Cyprus intends to visit the
island in the coming weeks," Annan was quoted as saying in his
latest report to the Security Council on his mission of good
offices in Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. chief said that in the last six months he and his
special adviser have tried to make the necessary arrangements for
the continuing and sustained process of direct negotiations
between the leaders of the Greek and Turkish Cypriots.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, all these efforts so far have not proved
sufficient to lead to a resumption of the process.
</P>
<P>
Annan said he strongly hopes that all parties involved will
abstain from any action which could further exacerbate tensions.
</P>
</TEXT>
