<HEADLINE> Vieri's Double Lifts Italy to 3-0 Win over Cameroon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTPELLIER, France, June 17 (Xinhua) -- A double from Christian
Vieri lifted Italy to a 3-0 victory over 10-men Cameroon in group B in
the World Cup finals here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Italy led the first half 1-0 on a goal from Luigi Di Biagio after
eight minutes when the AS Roma midfielder headed home a pass from
Roberto Baggio.
</P>
<P>
Cameroon was reduced to 10 men after Raymond Kalla Nkongo was given
the marching order in the 45th minute by Australian referee Edward
Lennie.
</P>
<P>
But the Indomitable Lions from the African continent rallied
strongly in the second half, almost equalizing with long-range blasts
from Joseph Job of French side Olympique Lyon and Patrick Mboma of
Japan's Gamba Osaka.
</P>
<P>
Juventus striker Alessandro Del Piero made his first appearance in
the competition when he replaced Roberto Baggio in the 65th minute.
</P>
<P>
He proved his value 10 minutes later, breaking off from the center
before feeding a ball to Vieri on the right to score.
</P>
<P>
Athletic Madrid forward Vieri was on target in the 89th minute,
this time slotting the ball home from in the area.
</P>
<P>
Vieri now tied Chile's Marcelo Salas for the leading scorer with
three goals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
